Broccoli chemical sulforaphane is known to block inflammation and damage to cartilage associated with arthritis . 
  But patients would have to eat several pounds of the vegetable every day to benefit . 
  Sulforphane in its natural form is also too unstable to turn into a medicine . 
  UK drug company Evgen Pharma has developed a stable synthetic version of the chemical that offers potential of a pill treatment . 
 